result.execSummary:
The defendant Jose Luis Prado-Estrada was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jose Luis Prado-Estrada in court with attorney Rod J Koenen.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and the Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:    COURT ORDERED THE Defendant to serve 50 DAYS in the House of Correction (HOC), consecutive to Count 4 credit for 1 day time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work, child care, and elder care.  REPORT DATE 11-25-2016 BY 05:00 pm (1700 hrs.) Court shall allow for GOOD TIME AND ELECTRONIC MONITORING (EM), if accepted by the Department.

AS TO COUNT 4:    COURT ORDERED THE Defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction (HOC), consecutive to Count 1.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work, child care, and elder care.  

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence, as to Count 4, and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 Months.

COURT ORDERED THE FOLLOWING:
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  As to Count 1,  ONLY, pay a fine of $350.00 plus costs, surcharges, assessments, supervision, and DNA fees out of bail on deposit, if any; and the balance due prior to the end of the probationary period as to Count 4.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.  
*  As to Count 4,  ONLY, Costs are waived. (indigent).
*  Maintain full time / part time employment and or schooling.
*  Maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
*  AODA assessment with follow up care and treatment.
*  Random urine screens with no positive results.  No association with drug users, drug dealers, drug houses, or drug dealings.
*  As to Count 1,  ONLY,   Defendant required to provide a biological specimen (DNA) to the State Crime Lab for testing.
*  As to Count 1,  ONLY,  12 MONTHS suspension driver's privileges.
*  As to Count 1,  ONLY,  12 MONTHS Ignition Interlock Device on the OWI.

Received and filed with the court:
